Title : Sadaqat Ashram
Text : {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}}
{{Use Indian English|date=August 2017}}
'''Sadaqat [[Ashram]]''' is located in [[Patna]], [[Bihar]], beside the main road of [[Digha, Patna|Digha]] area, on the banks of the River [[Ganges]], almost seven kilometres from the [[Patna Airport|airport]]. This was one of the residences of Dr. [[Rajendra Prasad]], the first President of India, who lived there after retirement and spent the last days of his life there.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-miscellaneous/this-day-that-age/article3423737.ece |title=This day that age |publisher=The Hindu |date=2012-05-16 |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

It was established by [[Mahatma Gandhi]] in 1921. Spread over 20 acres,<ref name="intoday1">{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/patna-sadaqat-ashram-where-freedom-fighters-spend-their-last-days-is-for-sale-by-bpcc/1/155464.html |title=Adobe of Indian freedom fighters at sale : HERITAGE - India Today |publisher=Indiatoday.intoday.in |date=2007-07-16 |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref> ashram's land was donated by his close associate Mulana Mazharul Haque's friend Khairun miyan to the national movement.<ref>http://www.iamin.in/en/patna-sahib/news/sadaqat-ashram-where-uprisings-freedom-movement-sprouted-43075</ref> During independence movement, Important meetings between eminent freedom fighters like Brajkishore Prasad, Maulana Mazharul Haque, Dr. Anugrah Narayan Sinha & Rajendra  Prasad  has taken place here. After Independence, [[Jayaprakash Narayan]] launched his historic movement during the 1970s from the Sadaqat Ashram.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/patnas-historic-ashram-in-danger/42973-3.html |title=Patna's historic Ashram in danger - IBNLive |publisher=Ibnlive.in.com |date=2007-06-20 |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bYBdK0algM8C&pg=PA133&lpg=PA133&dq=sadaqat+ashram+on+the+banks+of+ganga&source=bl&ots=1A7xTER8aK&sig=d91VbT9t49Qdht4J3V83QMWQGhY&hl=en&sa=X&ei=XTFhU-O2JoyTuATW3YGgCA&ved=0CG4Q6AEwBg |title=Meandering Pastures of Memories - Shovana Narayan - Google Books |publisher=Books.google.co.in |date= |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

==Present day==
Today, it is the headquarters of Bihar Vidyapeeth,<ref name="intoday1"/> a National University and [[Bihar Pradesh Congress Committee]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/patna/Bihar-leaders-celebrate-birth-anniversary-of-former-chief-minister-S-N-Sinha/articleshow/21048259.cms |title=Bihar leaders celebrate birth anniversary of former chief minister S N Sinha - The Times of India |publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=2013-07-13 |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref> The ashram now has a museum, the [[Rajendra Smriti Sangrahalaya]], that displays Rajendra Prasad's personal belongings and many historical things belonging to the freedom struggle of India. It attracts many tourists every year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mapsofindia.com/patna/places-of-interest/sadaqat-ashram.html |title=Sadaqat Ashram |publisher=Mapsofindia.com |date=2013-05-29 |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

